		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Which only means that "an NTSC video game" and "a PAL video game" have always been misnomers for "a 240p/480i video game" and "a 288p/576i video game", except in the case of early consoles such as the Atari 2600 that used significantly different palettes for the two color systems.

		

